---
source: src/cli/mod.rs, src/serve.rs, Cargo.toml
assertion: serve localhost is an honest defer-to-v2 command surface in v1
schema:
  command: ee serve --foreground --json
  envelope: ee.error.v2
  code: serve_unavailable_v1
  status: documented_stubbed
contracts:
  - ee serve --help is visible in default builds
  - ee serve --foreground --json emits ee.error.v2 with code serve_unavailable_v1
  - severity is low because direct CLI commands remain the supported v1 path
  - repair text tracks bd-3usjw.4 and docs/adr/0033-serve-localhost-v2-design.md
  - recovery actions point to direct CLI commands: ee context, ee search, ee status, and ee doctor
  - human output says the localhost HTTP adapter is planned for v2
  - no HTTP listener starts in v1 and no forbidden HTTP stack is introduced
  - serve adapter remains a wrapper boundary and must not add business logic
feature_requirements:
  - serve = [] feature flag in Cargo.toml
  - BuildFeature::new("serve", cfg!(feature = "serve")) in capabilities
  - FeatureEntry::new("serve", cfg!(feature = "serve"), "HTTP serve adapter")
  - forbidden dependencies not pulled: tokio, hyper, axum, tower, reqwest
  - top-level CLI command exists as an honest v1 unavailable surface
evidence:
  - Cargo.toml: serve = []
  - src/cli/mod.rs: Command::Serve and SERVE_UNAVAILABLE_CODE
  - src/serve.rs: SERVE_UNAVAILABLE_V1_CODE and serve_unavailable_v1_error
  - tests/fixtures/failure_modes/serve_unavailable_v1.json
  - scripts/vision-coverage.sh reports serve under documented_stubbed_surfaces
degraded_contract:
  - serve surface returns a deterministic unavailable error in v1
  - capabilities.features may still report the optional serve feature disabled
  - no HTTP server starts until the v2 ADR is implemented
